    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-12-10T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-12-10T20:00:00-05:00" n="616"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d616">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/3157: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Shaw</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-12-11T01:00:00+00:00"
                            >December 11, 1931—1 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 10—9:52 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>876. From Ambassador Dawes: Resolution unanimously adopted at this afternoon’s
                    meeting of the Council.<note n="77" xml:id="d616fn77">For text of the League
                        Council’s resolution adopted December 10, see <ref
                            target="frus1931-41v01#pg_59">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 59</ref>.</note> [Dawes.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Shaw</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
